VERSION "honda_civic_bosch_radar -- 36802-TBA Bosch FINE per-track object table (0x280 block). Hand-written (NOT generated; named without _generated so it is git-tracked and loaded via the file fallback, like acura_ilx_2016_nidec.dbc). FINE decode cross-car CONFIRMED 2026-06-07 (3 cars / 6 routes; 8905 cross-car tracks fused leadOne.dRel at R^2=0.975 -- radar-re/finerange-confirm/CONFIRM-REPORT.md). This SUPERSEDES the coarse 0x2C8/0x2C9 selected-lead as the RANGE source: range is now carried in B2:B3 of the b1==0x74 header frame of each 4-frame track record at a PHYSICALLY CALIBRATED scale (0.00357 m/unit, offset -3.0). 0x2C8/0x2C9 remain declared below ONLY as a dormant coarse reference; the parser does NOT read range from them. PHYSICAL BUS = openpilot CanBus.camera (rlog src=2), NOT CanBus.radar -- the Bus.radar key is only the DBC-name lookup. The frame counter is carried as CNTR (NOT COUNTER) and there is NO CHECKSUM signal on the fine frames -- opendbc auto-enforces the hardcoded Honda checksum/counter on honda_* DBCs and would DROP every frame on the exact names CHECKSUM/COUNTER; this radar's framing is its own and this is RX-only lead data, so we name around the trap and decode unconditionally."

